tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: Most parameters are within normal limits. Mildly elevated chloride, total cholesterol, and LDL cholesterol are noted, which may increase cardiovascular risk. Hemoglobin A1c is at the upper limit of normal, suggesting close monitoring for glucose metabolism is advisable. Renal and electrolyte status is stable. No acute abnormalities detected.
